  "abstract": "<p>The manuscript titled \"Genetic Dissection of Protein Content in Cowpea Using Custom-made NIRS equations and GWAS as a Model for Nutritional Breeding and Undergraduate Research Training\" examines the genetic basis of grain protein content in cowpea (black-eye pea), a key crop for food and nutrition security. The authors evaluated 287 diverse cowpea accessions using a species-specific near-infrared spectroscopy model with high accuracy to estimate protein levels.</p>\n",
